While much of Key West is catering now to the cruise ship business and has become more and more honky-tonk, this lovely hotel retains the former charm and quaintness of Key West in an upscale fashion.	Our only complaints were that there were no premium cable stations which is odd for a place of this caliber, and that the unheated pool should be heated so there are more swimming options.	it is amazing how quiet this hotel is and yet to close to the action.you can walk to anywhere.they also have a lovely upscale restaurant which should be sampled.beautifully prepared and delicious regional foods.